<comment datatype='string'>To test whether the ORFs downstream of the &lt;i&gt;rpoN&lt;/i&gt; gene are cotranscribed  and encode proteins, this region was subjected to Maxicell and T7 promoter analysis. The results show they are coexpressed with the &lt;i&gt;rpoN&lt;/i&gt; gene. 
&lt;p&gt;
The ORFV is the last ORF of the &lt;i&gt;rpoN&lt;/i&gt; operon, consistent with our identification of a likely rho-dependent terminator after ORFV.
&lt;p&gt;
The expression of the &lt;i&gt;rpoN&lt;/i&gt; gene was increased in mutants for two genes that encode two terminal oxidases, &lt;i&gt;cyoA&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;cydB&lt;/i&gt;, and in mutants of two transcriptional regulators, Fnr and Fur. However, it is unknown if the effects of the transcriptional regulators act directly on the gene expression; also, it is unknown which of the two promoters that transcribe the gene could  be regulated by the regulators [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21272324&quot;&gt;Kumar11&lt;/a&gt;].</comment>
